&lt;p&gt;With Hugo on the other hand, you &lt;em&gt;have&lt;/em&gt; to use GitHub actions. If you’ve never used CI before, this might seem daunting, but Hugo has &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/hosting-and-deployment/hosting-on-github/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;clear instructions&lt;/a&gt; on how to configure everything. They also provide a template workflow, which you can simply copy over to your repo. It took me about 10 minutes to first deploy the first version of this website.&lt;/p&gt;</description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://BillyDoesDev.github.io/blog/another_blog/featured.jpg"/></item></channel></rss>